Aaron,
I live in a wet climate up here in the PNW and I have found that if you are
using large volumes of air constantly, a water trap before and after is
necessary. I usually cycle my entire tank volume in one use and that sucks
in a large quantity of air in one shot, along with its moisture content.
67 Single Cab
71 Trike
VolksAir
Ray, Kent WA
The water is boiling, the frog just doesn't know it yet


